===Etymology===
From Middle English '''flour''' (flower, best of anything) < Old French '''flor''' < Latin accusative '''flōrem''' < nominative '''[[flos|flōs]]''' (flower) < Proto-Indo-European base '''[[*bhlo-]]''' (to blossom, flourish), extended form of '''[[*bhel-]]''' (to thrive, bloom).

